# AI-POWERED STUDENT DROPOUT PREDICTION AND COUNSELING SYSTEM

## 1. PROJECT TITLE

AI-Powered Student Dropout Prediction and Counseling System

---

## 2. PROBLEM STATEMENT

Student dropout is one of the major challenges faced by educational institutions worldwide. Factors such as poor attendance, low academic performance, financial difficulties, personal issues, lack of motivation, and insufficient academic support can increase the likelihood of students discontinuing their studies.

Traditional methods often identify at-risk students only after significant academic decline has occurred, making intervention less effective. Educational institutions require intelligent systems that can analyze student data and predict dropout risks at an early stage.

The AI-Powered Student Dropout Prediction and Counseling System aims to address this issue by leveraging Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, and Data Analytics to identify students at risk of dropping out, provide timely alerts to faculty and counselors, and support proactive intervention strategies to improve student retention and academic success.

---

## 3. PROJECT OBJECTIVES

### Primary Objectives

* Develop an intelligent student risk prediction platform.
* Predict students who are likely to drop out using Machine Learning algorithms.
* Analyze academic performance, attendance, and behavioral patterns.
* Generate student risk scores and classifications.
* Provide early alerts to faculty members and counselors.
* Recommend appropriate counseling and support measures.
* Monitor student progress continuously.
* Support data-driven educational decision-making.

### Secondary Objectives

* Improve student retention rates.
* Reduce dropout percentages.
* Enhance academic performance.
* Strengthen student counseling processes.
* Improve institutional efficiency and educational outcomes.

